			                <div class="section">
					                  <div class="section-title">POWERING UP</div>
							                  <div class="step">
									                        <div class="step-title"></div>
												                    <div class="step-image"><img src='https://dchtm6r471mui.cloudfront.net/hackpad.com_Sg7Iq7GM9Ju_p.243257_1419400644427_underside.JPG' />
														                          </div>
														                        <div class="step-text">
																	                          <p>Each L3D Cube comes with a 3-ft microUSB cable and 2A adapter.  5V, 500mA USB power can power the Default Demos and many of the apps you'll find on CubeTube - so your Cube can run off your computer, wall wart, or a battery pack. But we've also included the 2A adapter with 100VAC -  220VAC input for more intense visualizations (you will need to supply your own prong adapter if outside the US).</p>

																				  <p>Note 1:  there is a 1.7A current limit built into the baseboard of the 8x8x8 Cubes.
																				    </p>
																				  <p>Note 2:  there is a bypass built into the baseboard of the 8x8x8 L3D Cubes which allows advanced users to get around the current limit for super bright cubing.  Some of these modifications are popping up on the Forum [add link], check them out!</p>
																				                      </div>
																	                </div>
									              </div>
					            <div class="section">
						                      <div class="section-title">PLAYING DEFAULT DEMOS</div>
								                      <div class="step">
											                    <div class="step-title"></div>
													                        <div class="step-image"><img src='https://dchtm6r471mui.cloudfront.net/hackpad.com_Sg7Iq7GM9Ju_p.243257_1419398065591_tiltcontrolscreenshot.png' />
																                      </div>
																                    <div class="step-text">
																		      <p>The 8x8x8 L3D Cubes come pre-loaded with four demos:</p>
																		                             <ul>
																					           <li>Fireworks</li>
																						       <li>Zplasma</li>
																						           <li>Squarral</li>
																							       <li>Purple Rain (sound reactive)</li>
																							       </ul>
																					     <p>The four demos will loop forever by default. You can stop the loop and play just one selected demo by tilting left, right, and forward.</p>

																					     <p>The loop can be restarted by reconnecting to power.</p>

